
@startuml
' Aircraft Management System

class Aircraft {
  +name: String
  +type: String
  +yearOfManufacture: Integer
  +nextInspectionDate: Date
}

class Flight {
  +flightNumber: String
  +date: Date
}

class Passenger {
  +name: String
  +passportNumber: String
}

class Ticket {
  +ticketNumber: String
  +price: Double
  +upgradeDesired: Boolean
}

class PassengerAircraft {
  +numberOfSeats: Integer
}

class SeatCategory {
  +designation: String
  +hasEntertainment: Boolean
  +numberOfSeats: Integer
}

class Airline {
  +name: String
}

class FlightAttendant {
  +name: String
  +dateOfEmployment: Date
  +isChiefSteward: Boolean
}

class Pilot {
  +name: String
  +dateOfEmployment: Date
  +license: String
}

class Airport {
  +name: String
  +address: String
  +numberOfRunways: Integer
}

' Relationships

Aircraft "1" -- "0..*" Flight : has
Flight "1" -- "0..*" Passenger : includes
Passenger "1" -- "1" Ticket : has
Ticket "1" -- "1" SeatCategory : belongsTo

Aircraft "1" -- "1" PassengerAircraft : is a
PassengerAircraft "1" -- "0..*" SeatCategory : has

Aircraft "1" -- "1" Airline : belongsTo
Airline "1" -- "0..*" FlightAttendant : employs
Airline "1" -- "0..*" Pilot : employs

Flight "1" -- "0..*" FlightAttendant : has
Flight "1" -- "1" Pilot : hasCaptain
Flight "1" -- "0..2" Pilot : hasCoPilot

Aircraft "1" -- "0..1" Airport : hasHomeAirport
Flight "1" -- "1" Airport : hasDepartureAirport
Flight "1" -- "1" Airport : hasDestinationAirport

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:
- `Aircraft` can be a `PassengerAircraft`, which is an inheritance relationship.
- Each `Flight` is associated with multiple `Passengers` and `Tickets`.
- Each `Ticket` belongs to one `SeatCategory`, and each `SeatCategory` is part of a `PassengerAircraft`.
- An `Aircraft` is part of an `Airline`, which employs both `FlightAttendants` and `Pilots`.
- A `Flight` is managed by one `Pilot` (as captain) and optionally up to two `Pilots` (as co-pilots), and involves several `FlightAttendants`.

